Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Knowledge Journalizing Module - This JKM provides consistent journalizing procedures on IBM DB2 UDB tables
Restrictions: - When starting the journal on a model, tables no longer in the set are unjournalized, tables missing from the set are journalized. - If the table is already journalized and is present in another model, the current journal data will be lost and the table is transfered to the new journal set. - This Knowledge Module creates triggers on your source tables. Be sure to validate the scalability of your applications before releasing your developments in your production systems.

create trigger <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_UTRIGGER")%> after update on <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing NEW as NROW for each row mode db2sql insert into <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( WINDOW_ID, <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) values ( /* WINDOW_ID */ NULL, <%=snpRef.getColList("", "/* [COL_NAME] */\tNROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> )

select FULL_TABLE_NAME <%= snpRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") %> FULL_TABLE_NAME from <%=snpRef.getObjectName("L" ,"SNP_TMP_TABLE_LIST" , "W")%> <%= snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD") %> TMP where TMP.FULL_TABLE_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' and not exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_OBJECTS_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> OBJ, <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_TABLE_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TBL where TBL.FULL_TABLE_NAME = OBJ.FULL_TABLE_NAME and TBL.FULL_TABLE_NAME = TMP.FULL_TABLE_NAME and TBL.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>' and OBJ.FULL_OBJECT_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_UTRIGGER")%>' and OBJ.CDC_OBJECT_TYPE = 'JRN_FULL_UTRIGGER' )

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang
# Connect to the Source Database ie the one that hosts the journalized tables myCon = snpRef.getJDBCConnection("SRC")
# Create the list of Subscribers for a CDC Set lstSbs = [] <%= snpRef.getSubscriberList("" , "lstSbs.append('[SUBSCRIBER]')", "\n", "") %>

create table <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo( "CDC_SUBS_TABLE" )%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( CDC_SET_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "255", "0" )%> not null, /* Name of the CDC Set (Sunopsis model code) */ CDC_SUBSCRIBER <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "35", "0" )%> not null, /* Name of the subscriber who subscribed to the CDC Set */ CDC_REFDATE <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE")%> not null, /* Last update of the record */ MIN_WINDOW_ID <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Window Ids under this one should be ignored */ MAX_WINDOW_ID <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Maximum Window Id used by this subscription */ MAX_WINDOW_ID_DEL <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Maximum Window Id to take into consideration when looking at consistency for deletes */ MAX_WINDOW_ID_INS <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Maximum Window Id to take into consideration when looking at consistency for inserts / updates */ CDC_ROW_COUNT <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "10")%> not null, /* Number of rows in the journalizing tables for this subscription */ constraint PK_SNP_CDC_SBS primary key (CDC_SET_NAME, CDC_SUBSCRIBER) )

create table <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo( "CDC_SET_TABLE" )%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( CDC_SET_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "255", "0" )%> not null, /* Name of the CDC Set (Sunopsis model code) */ CUR_WINDOW_ID <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Last window Id that has been used */ CUR_WINDOW_ID_DEL <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Last Window Id used to compute delete consitency */ CUR_WINDOW_ID_INS <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> not null, /* Last Window Id used to compute inert / update consitency */ RETRIEVE_DATA <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, /* Command to execute in order to retrieve the journal data (used by the SnpsRetrieveJournalData API) */ REFRESH_ROW_COUNT <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, /* Command to execute in order to refresh the row count(used by the SnpsRefreshJournalData API) */ constraint PK_SNP_CDC_SET primary key (CDC_SET_NAME) )

create table <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_TABLE_TABLE")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( CDC_SET_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "255")%> not null, /* Name of the CDC Set (Sunopsis model code) */ FULL_TABLE_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalized table */ FULL_DATA_VIEW <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalizing data view */ RETRIEVE_DATA <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, /* Command to execute to retrieve the journal data (used by the SnpsRetrieveJournalData API) */ REFRESH_ROW_COUNT <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, /* Command to execute to refresh the row count (used by the SnpsRefresh RowCount API) */ constraint PK_SNP_CDC_TBL primary key (FULL_TABLE_NAME) )

create table <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_OBJECTS_TABLE")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( FULL_TABLE_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalized table */ CDC_OBJECT_TYPE <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "35")%> not null, /* Type of the object in the CDC framework */ FULL_OBJECT_NAME <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> not null, /* Complete name of the object */ DB_OBJECT_TYPE <%=snpRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "35")%>, /* RDBMS type of the object (ex : TABLE, VIEW, TRIGGER) */ constraint PK_SNP_CDC_OBJ primary key (FULL_TABLE_NAME, CDC_OBJECT_TYPE) )

update <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SET_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> CDC set CDC.RETRIEVE_DATA = NULL, CDC.REFRESH_ROW_COUNT = 'update <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> set CDC_ROW_COUNT = 0 where CDC_SUBSCRIBER = ''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'' and CDC_SET_NAME = ''<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>''' where CDC.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>'

insCmd = """insert into <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> (CDC_SET_NAME, CDC_SUBSCRIBER, CDC_REFDATE, MIN_WINDOW_ID, MAX_WINDOW_ID, MAX_WINDOW_ID_DEL, MAX_WINDOW_ID_INS, CDC_ROW_COUNT) select '<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>', cast (? as varchar(35)), current timestamp, CDC.CUR_WINDOW_ID, -1, -1, -1, 0 from <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SET_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> CDC where CDC.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>' """
selCmd = """select count('X') from <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> CDC where CDC.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=snpRef.getObjectName("L", snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>' and CDC.CDC_SUBSCRIBER = ? """
# Prepare the statements prepInsStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(insCmd) prepSelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(selCmd)
# Execute for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepSelStmt.setString(1, sbs) rs = prepSelStmt.executeQuery() rs.next() nbSubs = rs.getInt(1) if (nbSubs == 0): prepInsStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepInsStmt.executeUpdate()
prepInsStmt.close() prepSelStmt.close()
# commit the updates myCon.commit()

"""

	", "", "PK")%>, <%=snpRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]	" + snpRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUB, <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN left outer join <%=snpRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG on ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]	= TARG.[COL_NAME]", "
